WEBVTT

00:01.710 --> 00:04.796
(SINGING)
It seems today that all you see

00:04.880 --> 00:07.966
Is violence in movies and sex on TV

00:08.217 --> 00:11.678
But where are those
Good old-fashioned values

00:11.803 --> 00:14.348
ALL: On which we used to rely?

00:14.932 --> 00:17.851
Lucky there's a family guy

00:18.352 --> 00:21.605
Lucky there's a man who positively can do

00:21.730 --> 00:23.148
All the things that make us

00:23.232 --> 00:24.733
Laugh and cry

00:24.942 --> 00:29.905
ALL: He's a family guy!

00:35.452 --> 00:38.539
Hi, it's me, Peter, your TV cartoon pal.

00:38.622 --> 00:41.208
You know, Lois has been bitching lately
that I watch too much TV

00:41.291 --> 00:42.501
and don't read enough books.

00:42.584 --> 00:44.670
So, I went to the library
and picked up three books

00:44.753 --> 00:47.589
by the greatest author
of the last thousand years:

00:47.673 --> 00:49.174
Stephen King.

00:49.258 --> 00:51.301
And tonight, I'd like
to share them with you.

00:51.468 --> 00:54.054
We begin with a little tale
called "Stand By Me,"

00:54.263 --> 00:57.015
about four young boys
who went looking for a dead body

00:57.099 --> 00:59.226
and instead found themselves.

01:00.310 --> 01:01.854
And also a dead body.

01:05.315 --> 01:07.651
The year was 1955.

01:07.776 --> 01:10.320
And the voice in my head
was that of Richard Dreyfuss.

01:10.404 --> 01:13.740
RICHARD DREYFUSS: I never had friends
like the ones I had when I was 12.

01:13.824 --> 01:15.659
There was me, Petey LeChance...

01:15.742 --> 01:18.495
Anyone else fed up with this
oversaturation of media?

01:18.579 --> 01:20.581
Three channels and still nothing on.

01:20.664 --> 01:22.124
DREYFUSS: Then there was Joey Duchamps.

01:22.332 --> 01:24.293
The voice in his head was Roy Scheider.

01:24.376 --> 01:25.586
ROY SCHEIDER: How are you, Richard?

01:25.669 --> 01:26.879
DREYFUSS: Fine, Roy, how are you?

01:26.962 --> 01:28.255
SCHEIDER: Good, good.

01:28.338 --> 01:30.632
We should grab a drink sometime
and catch up,

01:30.716 --> 01:32.301
maybe reminisce about Jaws.

01:32.384 --> 01:34.428
DREYFUSS: Great, you should
give mea call sometime.

01:34.511 --> 01:35.971
My number's 555...

01:36.180 --> 01:39.641
SCHEIDER: Wait, wait. What? 555?
DREYFUSS: Uh, yeah.

01:39.725 --> 01:40.934
SCHEIDER: You know what, Richard,

01:41.018 --> 01:42.728
if you don't want to have drinks,
just say so.

01:42.811 --> 01:44.271
You don't have to be a dick about it.

01:44.354 --> 01:46.690
Oh, please, make the voices stop!

01:47.107 --> 01:49.026
DREYFUSS: And then
there wasQuag Chambers.

01:49.109 --> 01:50.903
He was the leader of our gang.

01:51.069 --> 01:52.654
He had sex when he was five

01:52.738 --> 01:54.615
and committed his first rape
when he was ten.

01:54.698 --> 01:56.825
Rape, of course, being legal in the '50s.

01:57.159 --> 01:59.036
(CHUCKLES) Beat those cards, fellas!

01:59.119 --> 02:00.162
(LAUGHS)

02:00.245 --> 02:01.663
Giggity, giggity, '50s giggity.

02:01.747 --> 02:02.998
Hey, you guys...

02:03.081 --> 02:06.210
DREYFUSS: Finally, there was Cleve Brown,
my pudgy, Black friend.

02:06.502 --> 02:09.546
I can still see him now,
all pudgy and Black.

02:09.838 --> 02:11.965
Cleve, please,
we're busy looking at Playboy.

02:12.049 --> 02:14.092
Look at the way these women
starve themselves.

02:14.176 --> 02:16.386
This one can't be more than 180 pounds.

02:16.470 --> 02:18.555
This is way better than Playboy.

02:18.722 --> 02:20.766
Do you guys want to see a dead body?

02:20.849 --> 02:22.518
Cleve, it's 1955.

02:22.601 --> 02:23.852
Please reenter the clubhouse

02:23.936 --> 02:25.854
in a more stereotypically
animated fashion.

02:28.106 --> 02:31.109
Lord Almighty, I done seen me
a dead body down by the lake!

02:31.360 --> 02:33.278
Sure 'nough,
I thought I'd go deaf and dumb

02:33.362 --> 02:34.571
when I saw me that dead bod...

02:34.655 --> 02:36.657
Cleve, calm down!
You're not making any sense!

02:36.949 --> 02:40.285
BUDDY HOLLY: (SINGING)
Everyday, it's a-gettin' closer

02:41.036 --> 02:43.622
DREYFUSS: Anything was possible
as we set out that day.

02:43.705 --> 02:46.500
Except contracting AIDS,
because AIDS had not yet

02:46.583 --> 02:48.669
been invented by the government
in an effort

02:48.752 --> 02:50.796
to eradicate the homosexual community.

02:51.171 --> 02:53.215
ALL: (SINGING)
Have gun, will travel

02:53.298 --> 02:56.385
Reads the card of a man

02:56.677 --> 03:01.515
A knight without armor
In a savage land

03:01.598 --> 03:02.933
Okay, I got another one.

03:03.308 --> 03:04.852
(SINGING) Show me that smile again

03:04.935 --> 03:06.770
Ooh, show me that smile

03:06.979 --> 03:10.941
Don't waste another minute on your crying

03:11.692 --> 03:14.695
DREYFUSS: We decided to cut through
Old Man Pressman's junkyard,

03:14.778 --> 03:16.071
even though legend had it

03:16.154 --> 03:18.657
that any kid caught
scaling the fence ran the risk

03:18.740 --> 03:21.076
of being attacked by
the old man's dog,

03:21.326 --> 03:24.663
who would charge to the cry
of"Chopper, sic balls."

03:25.455 --> 03:27.291
I got a bad feeling about this.

03:27.666 --> 03:29.751
Hey! What are you kids doing?

03:29.835 --> 03:31.128
Oh, no, it's him!

03:31.211 --> 03:33.964
That's right. I'm Old Man Pressman.
I own the junkyard.

03:34.047 --> 03:38.594
I'm cranky 'cause all my stuff is junk.
Why can't I have nice things?

03:39.219 --> 03:40.721
Chopper, sic 'em! Sic 'em, boy!

03:40.804 --> 03:43.182
-(BARKING)
-(ALL SCREAMING)

03:46.727 --> 03:49.771
DREYFUSS: Now, he said, "Sic 'em, boy,"
but what I heard was,

03:49.855 --> 03:52.941
"Chopper, talk todisfigured
World War II veterans

03:53.025 --> 03:54.568
"who aren't as bitter as they should be."

03:55.068 --> 03:56.737
Glad I could do my part.

03:56.820 --> 03:58.572
I think you may have done too much.

03:59.406 --> 04:01.408
RADIO ANNOUNCER:
Hey, how about this brand new thing

04:01.491 --> 04:02.618
called rock and roll?

04:02.826 --> 04:05.746
Even though it was just invented,
we already remember it fondly.

04:05.996 --> 04:08.332
Here's Little Richard
with "Piano Riff Woo!"

