05:06.640 --> 05:08.976
(SCREAMING) My legs!

05:09.977 --> 05:13.522
(SLOWLY) Another train!

05:13.981 --> 05:16.024
(SCREAMING)

05:16.108 --> 05:19.111
What an odd, clustered train schedule!

05:20.070 --> 05:21.905
Hey, sorry you got paralyzed, Joey.

05:21.989 --> 05:23.407
Oh, it's all right.

05:23.490 --> 05:26.118
Thanks for going all the way back
to the junkyard to get me this wheelchair.

05:26.201 --> 05:28.036
Boy, was Old Man Pressman angry.

05:28.495 --> 05:30.455
Ooh!

05:34.376 --> 05:36.211
Well, there it is.

05:36.378 --> 05:37.963
DREYFUSS: None of us could breathe.

05:38.130 --> 05:40.799
The twisted and mangled body
we had come to see

05:40.883 --> 05:43.093
was far more disgusting
than any of us

05:43.177 --> 05:44.386
could ever have imagined.

05:45.888 --> 05:47.347
CLEVE: He's nasty.

05:47.848 --> 05:49.683
Out of my way, you little pipsqueaks.

05:49.766 --> 05:51.894
I'm taking credit
for finding this body.

05:51.977 --> 05:54.771
-(KIDS GASP)
-DREYFUSS: It was the meanest guy in town,

05:55.063 --> 05:56.899
Ace, and his whole gang:

05:56.982 --> 06:00.986
Beast-Man, Mer-Man,
and forsome reason Norm from Cheers.

06:01.069 --> 06:03.113
Hey, gang.
What, are we beating somebody up?

06:03.405 --> 06:06.074
Now get lost. We'll take it from here.

06:07.242 --> 06:09.328
-(GASPS)
-(GUNSHOT)

06:09.912 --> 06:13.874
Kiss my grits, you cheap dime store hood.

06:14.249 --> 06:15.834
This ain't over, LeChance.

06:16.251 --> 06:18.712
I mean, you have a gun
right now, but tomorrow,

06:18.795 --> 06:21.256
I'll get a gun and come
to your house and kill you.

06:21.465 --> 06:22.758
Oh.

06:22.841 --> 06:24.676
Yeah, I guess you could do that, huh?

06:24.760 --> 06:26.386
I mean, we live in the same town.

06:26.470 --> 06:29.264
And I can't just be on my guard
for the rest of my life.

06:29.389 --> 06:32.392
Boy, that is a major hole in this story.
Okay, take the body.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.481
DREYFUSS: We never forgot
that wonderful summer,

06:37.564 --> 06:40.108
and eventually we all went
our separate ways.

06:40.192 --> 06:42.778
Joey learned to live
without the use of his legs,

06:42.861 --> 06:46.448
and even went on to create
a wheelchair-type rugby game

06:46.532 --> 06:49.201
called "Don't Feel Sorry for Us Ball."

06:49.368 --> 06:52.704
Cleve grew up and went on
to marry Rebecca Romjin.

06:52.788 --> 06:55.165
Actually, I'm not even joking about that.

06:55.249 --> 06:59.086
The fat kid from Stand By Me
is now marriedto Rebecca Romjin.

06:59.169 --> 07:02.756
Can you believe that? I swear to God.
Look it up on the Internet.

07:02.840 --> 07:04.174
Doesn't that piss you off?

07:04.633 --> 07:07.803
Quag grew up to become
a famous Hollywood actor.

07:07.886 --> 07:09.721
Unfortunately, about a week ago,

07:09.805 --> 07:12.891
he took an overdose of designer
drugs at the Viper Room.

07:13.392 --> 07:15.686
He died on the curb outside.

07:16.186 --> 07:18.856
And now we're left with
a hare-lipped reminder

07:18.939 --> 07:20.315
of what might have been.

07:20.399 --> 07:22.693
(COMEDY TRUMPET PLAYS)

07:24.903 --> 07:27.030
Hi. Welcome back from commercials.

07:27.322 --> 07:29.116
Joaquin Phoenix,
if you're still watching,

07:29.199 --> 07:31.285
you are a good sport and a trouper.

07:31.368 --> 07:34.454
And you passed our test.
And you can be our friend.

07:34.746 --> 07:38.166
And now for a segment we like
a little less than the first and the last.

07:38.250 --> 07:39.626
Here's Misery.

07:45.632 --> 07:46.717
Marcia, I've done it.

07:46.800 --> 07:48.677
I've finished the book,
and Snuggly Jeff is dead,

07:48.760 --> 07:50.304
and the readers are just gonna love it.

07:50.387 --> 07:52.848
Paul, I still wish I could
talk you out of this.

07:52.931 --> 07:56.059
Snuggly Jeff is the most successful
children's book series ever.

07:56.143 --> 07:58.353
Yeah, but I want to get into
writing more serious stuff.

07:58.437 --> 08:00.022
You know, something where
the reader doesn't have

08:00.105 --> 08:01.732
a load in his pants
while he's looking at it.

08:01.815 --> 08:03.483
Well, we'll talk about
it when you get back.

08:09.239 --> 08:10.449
RADIO ANNOUNCER: This just in.

08:10.532 --> 08:13.327
The weather service has reported
a big snow storm on its way.

08:16.538 --> 08:18.040
Oh, my God! Stephen King!

08:18.332 --> 08:19.416
(TIRES SCREECHING)

08:19.499 --> 08:20.792
(SCREAMS)

08:22.127 --> 08:23.545
Hey, this would make a neat story!

08:25.964 --> 08:27.007
Done.

08:47.069 --> 08:49.947
I'm your number one fan.
I'm your number one fan.

08:50.197 --> 08:51.532
I'm your number one fan.

08:52.199 --> 08:53.534
(GROANS)

08:54.076 --> 08:56.453
Who... Who are you?

08:56.537 --> 08:58.914
I'm Stewie Wilkes. I saved your life.

08:58.997 --> 09:01.834
You were in a terrible car accident
and you broke both your legs.

09:02.668 --> 09:04.795
I taste lipstick. Am I wearing lipstick?

09:04.878 --> 09:06.129
Not anymore.

09:09.633 --> 09:12.636
Um, Paul, quick question,
and feel free to say no.

09:12.719 --> 09:16.390
But I couldn't help but notice the new
Snuggly Jeff manuscript in your bag,

09:16.515 --> 09:19.643
and I was wondering if I could read it,
then kill you if I hate it?

09:19.726 --> 09:21.103
Well, I guess that'd be okay.

09:21.186 --> 09:22.604
Oh, thank you, thank you, thank you!

09:22.688 --> 09:24.690
Can I read it while I touch
your ear and suck my thumb?

09:24.773 --> 09:26.817
-Uh, I guess.
-Oh, goody, goody!

09:29.945 --> 09:31.029
(CHUCKLES)

09:32.948 --> 09:34.032
(CHUCKLES)

09:36.577 --> 09:38.412
(CHUCKLES)

09:39.204 --> 09:40.956
(SIGHS)

09:41.707 --> 09:43.333
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

09:48.505 --> 09:49.756
Stewie?

09:49.840 --> 09:53.177
I just finished the book,
you dirty birdie.

09:53.510 --> 09:55.888
How could you? He can't be dead.

09:55.971 --> 09:58.307
Snuggly Jeff cannot be dead!

09:58.390 --> 09:59.766
(SCREAMS)

09:59.850 --> 10:02.644
Look, Stewie, I've gone as far
as I can with Snuggly Jeff,

10:02.728 --> 10:04.605
and I... I want to write
something more serious.

10:05.355 --> 10:08.525
Well, you are gonna write Snuggly Jeff
back to life, Mr. Man.

10:08.609 --> 10:10.402
Look, Stewie, first of all,
you're insane.

10:10.485 --> 10:12.988
And second of all,
I have to be inspired before I write.

10:13.071 --> 10:14.656
Well, how about a little TV?

10:15.824 --> 10:18.202
ANNOUNCER:
We now return to Magnum B.M.

10:18.619 --> 10:21.830
Magnum, I found a fingerprint
smudge at the crime scene.

10:21.914 --> 10:23.790
Do you have poo on your hands?

10:24.249 --> 10:25.334
A little.

10:25.501 --> 10:28.253
(CLASSIC DETECTIVE
TV DRAMA THEME PLAYS)

10:32.007 --> 10:34.426
No, no, no. This won't do, Paul.

10:34.510 --> 10:35.761
You can't just have Snuggly Jeff

10:35.844 --> 10:38.180
magically brought back to life
by a child's wish.

10:38.347 --> 10:40.390
-It's insulting to the reader.
-What do you mean?

10:40.474 --> 10:42.142
Well, it's just bad storytelling.

10:42.226 --> 10:43.894
Let's see. How can I explain this to you?

10:43.977 --> 10:46.104
-Did you ever see the movie Contact?
-Yeah.

10:46.188 --> 10:49.149
So, like, they spent a trillion
dollars building this mile-high

10:49.233 --> 10:52.319
space machine and Jake Busey blows it up,
so now, they're all like,

10:52.402 --> 10:54.738
"Oh, no. We can't use the space machine."

10:54.821 --> 10:57.407
But then this other guy's like,
"Hey, it just so happens,

10:57.491 --> 11:00.494
"I built another identical
trillion-dollar space machine

11:00.577 --> 11:02.538
"at my own expense
on the other side of the world."

11:02.746 --> 11:05.082
And we're supposed to believe
no one noticed that?

11:05.332 --> 11:07.543
Well, I stood up in the theater,
and I said,

11:07.626 --> 11:10.629
"No! You can't go into space
because the machine

11:10.712 --> 11:13.924
"already got blown up
by Jake cock-a-doody Busey!"

11:14.424 --> 11:15.592
Start over!

11:15.843 --> 11:17.386
Fine. But you're going
to have to go into town

11:17.469 --> 11:18.971
and get me some more paper. I'm all out.

11:19.263 --> 11:20.264
I don't know, Paul.

11:20.347 --> 11:21.849
Let me see if I can get
the Big Wheel started.

11:24.184 --> 11:25.519
(IMITATING ENGINE STALLING)

11:25.602 --> 11:27.312
Oh, I don't know, Paul. It's not starting.

11:27.563 --> 11:28.939
(IMITATING ENGINE STALLING)

11:29.022 --> 11:30.357
Oh, I'm afraid I'm going to flood it.

11:30.440 --> 11:31.567
(IMITATING ENGINE STALLING)

11:31.817 --> 11:33.610
(IMITATING ENGINE STARTING)

11:33.694 --> 11:35.821
Okay. I got it now.
I'll see you in a bit.

11:35.904 --> 11:37.447
(WHEELS SQUEAKING)

12:11.815 --> 12:12.983
(CHUCKLING)

12:13.066 --> 12:14.526
He's too big for that car.

12:14.818 --> 12:15.944
-(FOOTSTEP APPROACHING)
-(GASPS)

12:23.827 --> 12:26.371
-Mr. Sheldon?
-Oh, my God. I'm saved.

12:26.455 --> 12:27.956
Let's get out of here
before Stewie gets back.

12:28.373 --> 12:29.833
-(GUNSHOTS)
-(SCREAMING)

12:31.210 --> 12:32.544
Ahh! My legs!

12:33.045 --> 12:36.215
Now I'm going to have to spend
the rest of my life in a wheelchair.

12:36.507 --> 12:37.591
No, you're not.

12:43.347 --> 12:45.307
Well, that's it, Stewie.
The book is done.

12:45.390 --> 12:46.433
Can I go now?

12:46.517 --> 12:48.519
Oh, no, Paul. I'm not stupid.

12:48.769 --> 12:51.104
If I let you go, you'll just
run straight to the police

12:51.188 --> 12:52.981
and tell them I kidnapped you
and held you hostage

12:53.065 --> 12:54.399
and fondled you while you were asleep.

12:54.566 --> 12:55.776
No, I won't... Wait. What?

12:55.859 --> 12:57.194
You'll tell them that
while you were sleeping,

12:57.277 --> 12:59.071
I did things to you
that you don't remember.

12:59.154 --> 13:01.406
You fondled me while I was asleep?

13:01.573 --> 13:03.116
-Yeah.
-I don't think I like that.

13:03.367 --> 13:04.409
Well, it's done.

13:05.744 --> 13:07.538
(CLASSIC DETECTIVE
TV DRAMA THEME PLAYS)

13:11.708 --> 13:14.253
Everybody still awake?
All right. Big finish.

13:14.378 --> 13:15.921
Now, you remember
that Stephen King story

13:16.004 --> 13:17.464
when the guy went up to the empty hotel

13:17.548 --> 13:18.799
and there were those creepy twins

13:18.882 --> 13:20.217
and the guy was running
around with that ax

13:20.300 --> 13:21.593
and the kid talked to his finger?

13:21.677 --> 13:23.428
Aw, can't you see Stewie doing that?

13:24.054 --> 13:25.806
Well, here's The Shawshank Redemption.

13:37.317 --> 13:38.986
(INMATES YELLING)

13:43.907 --> 13:46.535
RED: The first time I laid eyes
on Andy Dufresne,

13:46.785 --> 13:48.370
I didn't think much of him.

13:48.829 --> 13:50.497
He was a fat drink of water.

13:51.081 --> 13:53.375
The kind of drink of water
that you know your friend got

13:53.458 --> 13:55.794
from the bathroom
and not from the kitchen.

13:56.587 --> 13:59.798
Five packs of cigarettes
says the fat one breaks first tonight.

13:59.882 --> 14:02.134
You're on. I'll take
the Don-Martin-looking one.

14:08.265 --> 14:11.810
A month went by before Andy
said two words to somebody.

14:12.144 --> 14:14.730
As it turned out,
that somebody was me.

14:15.063 --> 14:16.440
Vagina boob.

14:16.982 --> 14:20.152
Later, Andy came back
with more than two words.

14:20.485 --> 14:22.779
I understand you're a man
who knows how to get things.

14:22.863 --> 14:26.033
I've been known to procure
various and sundry items.

14:26.116 --> 14:28.202
I... I don't understand
what you just said.

14:28.285 --> 14:29.745
I need stuff. Can you get it?

14:29.828 --> 14:30.954
What do you need?

14:31.038 --> 14:32.831
